graphTitleActiveCasesDesc.other: Active cases per day. üëâ This is the curve we have to flatten. The active cases are the people that currently have the virus, calculated as the total cases minus the recovered and deaths.

graphTitleDailyActiveCasesDesc.other: In each day, number of new active cases (people with the virus) compared to the previous day. A negative number means that the number of people with the virus decreased that day.

graphTitleDailyCasesDesc.other: Number of new cases in each day. Includes cases reported after the MSP report.

graphTitleDailyHospitalizationsDesc.other: Number of people in intermediate care and intensive care each day.

graphTitleDailyHospitalizationsPercentDe.other: Percentage of hospitalizations of active cases on each day.

graphTitleDailyPositivesDesc.other: Of all the tests performed each day, what percentage of tests where positive on that day.

graphTitleDailyTestsDesc.other: Number of tests carried out each day and how many of them were positive.

graphTitleDailyTestsNewDesc.other: Number of tests carried out each day. New tests reported out of date are not considered due to lack of information.

graphTitleHealthcareWorkersDesc.other: Number of new cases in each day that correspond to healthcare workers. New cases reported out of date are not considered due to lack of information.

graphTitleHealthcareWorkersPercentDesc.other: Of the new cases of each day, what percentage correspond to healthcare workers on that day. New cases reported out of date are not considered due to lack of information.

graphTitleRegionActiveCases.other: Active cases per million inhabitants in the region

graphTitleRegionActiveCasesDesc.other: Comparison of active cases (people with the virus) per million inhabitants in the countries of the region.

graphTitleRegionCases.other: Cumulative cases per million inhabitants in the region

graphTitleRegionCasesDesc.other: Comparison of cumulative cases per million inhabitants in the countries of the region.

graphTitleRegionDeaths.other: Deaths per million inhabitants in the region

graphTitleRegionDeathsDesc.other: Comparison of deaths per million inhabitants in the countries of the region.

graphTitleTotalCasesDesc.other: On each day, the total sum of confirmed cases, recovered and deaths up to that day.

graphTitleTotalTestsDesc.other: Comparison of all tests performed so far: percentage of positives and negatives.

graphTitleTotalsDesc.other: Comparison of the total cases registered so far: percentage of active cases, recovered and deaths.

graphDeathsDesc.other: Total deaths by age ranges and sex.

graphPositivityRateDesc.other: On each day, percentage of positive tests done that day. For this calculation, it is assumed that the total of positive tests corresponds to the number of new cases that day due to lack of information. New cases and tests reported out of date are not considered due to lack of information.

graphDailyVacsDesc.other: Number of administered vaccines per day, discriminated by vaccine type.

graphDailyDoseDesc.other: Total first and second dose per day

graphTotalVacsDesc.other: Total of administered vaccines, discriminated by vaccine type.

positivesAndCasesInfo.other: ‚ö†Ô∏è Until 04/08/2020 the number of cases (people with the virus) was not reported, but the number of positive tests. There are people with the virus that were tested positive more than once. Therefore until 4/8, cases (people with the virus) are assumed as the positive tests due to lack of information.

deathsInfo.other: ‚ö†Ô∏è On 02/22/2021 the MSP through the SINAE reported an incorrect death but did not indicate which one. On the other hand, on 03/25/2021 it reported 13 deaths, but only listed 12. Furthermore, on 04/09/2021 it reported 36 deaths from the past, but did not list them. On 04/10/2021 an incorrect death was removed. On 04/13/2021, one more deceased was listed (or one less was counted). On 04/18/2021 listed two less deceased. On 04/26/2021, 04/27/2021 and 05/02/2021 an incorrect deceased was listed each day (it is not known which one). On 05/08/2021 an incorrect death was removed. On 05/23/2021 an incorrect deceased was listed. On 01/06/2021 and 03/06/2021 two incorrect deaths were removed each day. An extra death was listed on 06/10/2021. An incorrect death was removed on 06/11/2021. Two incorrect deaths were removed on 06/14/2021. On 06/23/2021, 06/30/2021 and 07/01/2021 an incorrect death was removed each day. On 07/06/2021 and 07/07/2021, one more deceased was listed (or one less was counted). On 07/19/2021, 07/30/2021, 07/31/2021, 08/23/2021, 10/14/2021, 10/24/2021 and 11/19/2021 an incorrect death was removed each day. On 12/05/2021 a late death was added but wan't reported. For these reasons, the death chart "Deaths by age " does not add up the total number of deaths.

regionTitle.other: Comparison to the countries of the region

unreportedPositiviesInfo.other: ‚ö†Ô∏è As of 06/15 SINAE stopped reporting the daily and accumulated positive tests. Therefore, the tests graphs are updated until 06/14.

vaccinationProgressFirstDoseDesc.other: Percentage of the population that received at least one dose.

vaccinationProgressSecondDoseDesc.other: Percentage of the population that received two doses.

vaccinationProgressBoosterDoseDesc.other: Percentage of the population that received a booster dose (third dose).

harvardIndexDesc.other: Risk level according to the average of new cases per 100,000 inhabitants in the last 7 days. As of 11/4/2022 the color scheme was changed according to the GUIAD criteria.

unreliableData.other: On 04/09/2021, the MSP published a report updating the data from 03/01/2021 to 04/08/2021, which shows inconsistencies with the rest of the known data. For this reason, the historical data on this site is only based on the original daily reports until the differences are clarified. This means that almost all the graphs that use historical data are not correct in the indicated period due to lack of information.

vacErrorsInfo.other: The totals of the vaccination charts may differ with between them, following the official source.

vacetaDesc.other: Estimated date when the second dose will be given to 75% of the population, based on data from the last 28 days.
